'DESCRIPTION', &
'  EPSILON(3) returns the floating point relative accuracy. It is the nearly', &
'  negligible number relative to 1 such that 1+ LITTLE_NUMBER is not equal to', &
'  1; or more precisely', &
'', &
'        real( 1.0, kind(x)) + epsilon(x) /= real( 1.0, kind(x))', &
